Anonymous Fri 18 Sep 2020 20:44:59 No.32869066 Report
Quoted By: >>32869394
Since the last thread 404'd while I was typing...

>>32866968
That's a great setup, and a very solid foundation to build a story on. I guess the problem you're having is the story itself? Here's what I've learned from writing for /hmofa/: it's not always you know what you want. Sometimes the reason I blank on where to go next in the story, is because I honestly don't care much for what's going on at the moment. It could be mundane details, a safe plot or just a very by-the-numbers development, but either way it's not what I wanted to write. If you're struggling with character development, it might be the context more than the actions, and by changing the context you might find the rest to be a lot easier. That's not to say you should shy away from anything challenging, but you also shouldn't write if you're not enjoying the process. Perhaps thrusting the protagonist into some larger plot, maybe by having them be kidnapped or force them to run for the lives, might be the spark you need. At least that's how my brain works
Anonymous
